# Shopify App Proxy → Supabase Edge Function bridge.
#
# The storefront proxies POST https://dropdeadextensions.com/apps/apply/change-password
# to https://apply.dropdeadextensions.com/change-password (this origin). Without
# this rewrite the request falls through to index.html and returns 200 text/html,
# which the theme JS rejects. Forwarding to the Supabase Edge Function (where
# `change-password` is configured with verify_jwt = false) makes the route return
# the JSON contract documented in docs/contracts/account-change-password.md.
#
# Status 200 = full proxy: preserves method, body, and query string (Shopify's
# signed `signature`, `logged_in_customer_id`, `shop`, `timestamp`, `path_prefix`
# all flow through to the function for HMAC verification).
/change-password  https://qsunfiextzzdxnsyrkkc.supabase.co/functions/v1/change-password  200!
